<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 02 at 8:43PM MDT until July 02 at 9:15PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 915 PM MDT
FOR WEST CENTRAL TOOLE COUNTY...
At 842 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles southwest
of Kevin, or 10 miles east of Cut Bank, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Shelby and Ethridge.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
